I took my girlfriend here for Valentine's Day in 2019 and it was really great. We loved it and had a such a good time that we decided to go back in 2020 on Valentine's day on a double date. I made the reservation on February 3rd for 4 people at 9:00pm, as we couldn't make the other option of 5pm. We arrived around 8:50 to find a line out the door. I wasn't worried because we had reservations but upon telling the host our reservation seemed to have been lost, as countless other people also had 9pm reservations. It seemed like she was blaming me by asking if I received confirmation, however they took my credit card number when I made the reservation and said I'd be charged $40 if I cancelled, so I was not expecting any sort of confirmation.  To my chagrin, not only was our reservation lost, but everyone gathered in the tiny space seemed to ALSO have reservations. People had been waiting for 45 minutes who had reservations. I was not about to make girlfriend wait that long when it was already 9pm. The hostess had said she would talk to someone but when I asked her twenty minutes later if there was an update she seemed to not remember me at all. I explained our reservation was lost and she had said she would handle it.  Meanwhile, people are holding the door open and it's 8 degrees outside so everyone sitting and standing by the door was freezing. We kept pestering the host and at 9:30 she managed to get us seated a few rows from the door. Along with everyone in our section, we reamined cold for quite some time. It was then another 15 minutes before we were acknowledged and 25 before we were able to put in an order for apps and wine.  It could have been resolved if they would have listened to customer complaints asking for the door to be closed. If a discount or free drink/app was offered as an apology maybe that would have slightly offset the horrible experience on a high pressure romantic night, but management did not seem to consider any of this. Although the food was great, I am very hesitant to go back after this experience.

Super 😥 disappointed.  The service was bad and the food was midiocre. We'd been here before with my brother and his wife and the service was pretty good and the food was amazing so I decided to take my Hubby back for his birthday. When we arrived we were happy to discover it was a slow night thinking this would equate to fast seating and attentive service - nope!  The host was flat and made us wait at the bar although the place was more than half empty. He then came and got us and told us he'd seat us but, then instead proceeded to look something and make calls for a random passerby and then made small talk with an exciting customer. He wasn't moved in the least with its just standing there in front of him watching the whole scene. He just ignored us until my husband asked him excuse me, did you have a table for us? Not a good feeling.  After finally seating us in the half empty restaurant we sat and watched idle waitstaff stand against the back wall, refill water,  and check on already serviced patrons.  Our waiter never came. Again my husband after about 15 minutes had to ask the waiter for the table less than a half foot away from us if he could get our waiter for us to which he replied, "oh you need a waiter?  I be your waiter, sure no problem" and shrugged his shoulders as if he was doing us a favor. So I told no it's ok, please just get our waiter to which he repeated his previous statement. I then asked him so,  are you our waiter?  Because I really couldn't belive he was,  given the number of times he walked past us making eye contact knowing we had been waiting awhile. Again he just shrugged and responded "sure."  Really? I was so annoyed! Not a good feeling.  I'll end this review with: the food took forever and our steaks were tough but, at least they were tasty. It was a disheartening birthday celebration we left wishing we'd stayed home. Not a good feeling.

Not sure why this place has negative reviews. I liked all the food that I had. Went here with mum and brother.  Place itself doesnt look like it would be tres awesome from the outside. It looks dark at lonely at best. However, the inside belies this. It has a long bar the moment you enter, but it reminds me of the bars in London - dark wood and sleek. Nice decor too. We got a table at the back near the patio. I liked the low lighting and they light a pretty bright table candle for you to read the menu. Good idea to come here for a date!  We had the El Filet, the canneloni stuffed with ground beef and the Mil Hojas for dessert. For me, the canneloni was a little of a miss. But the meat made up for it, it was DELISH - came with tons of gravy, perfectly cooked and super juicy. Had spinach mashed potatoes on the side too - GET THIS DISH FOR SURE. The Mil Hojas was outstanding too.  I'll be back Folklore, thanks for the meal!
